\section{Case Demonstration of the Logic \& Summarization Agent}
\label{app:logic_case}

This appendix presents a concrete, end-to-end example of our three-step pipeline. 
Given an opponent's debate statement, we first extract pseudo-first-order predicates $\mathcal{P}_{\text{opp}}$, then derive a natural-language reasoning chain $\tau_{\text{opp}}$, and finally identify logical flaws $\mathcal{L}$.

